(power_clock, area_cell_area).explanation: Clock power and cell area are both outcomes of design complexity but clock power consumption does not directly determine the physical area occupied by standard cells;

(power_clock, area_cell_count).explanation: Clock power consumption and the number of standard cells are independent design metrics that both result from overall processor complexity rather than one causing the other;

(power_clock, power_pad).explanation: Clock power and pad power represent different power consumption components in processor design that are determined independently by their respective design parameters;
